{
  "texts": [
    "We encourage the readers to explore some of the classic attacks in the DP literature (Dinur & Nissim, 2003; Dwork et al., 2017) and their implications in the context of US census (Garfinkel et al., 2019) for a broader exposure.",
    "MIA aims to infer whether a data point was used to train a target machine learning model or not.",
    "These attacks can lead to substantial privacy concerns for the individuals involved.",
    "For instance, upon ascertaining that a clinical record was used in training a model associated with a specific disease, membership inference attacks may deduce, with a high probability, that the individual linked to the clinical record has the disease.",
    "Prior works (Carlini, Chien, et al., 2021; Jayaraman et al., 2020; Sablayrolles et al., 2019; Shokri et al., 2017; Watson et al., 2021; Yeom et al., 2018) private image data from trained image classifiers (Balle et al., 2022; Haim et al., 2022)."
  ]
}